text_Andesite: Closely resembles granite and has a grey color to it. There are lighter areas but never completely white.
text_Diorite: Has 2 distinctive colors often contrasting light/dark. Has notable sploches and lighter color seems to be the majority.

text_Basalt: Resembles a type of sandstone with grain. It has darker colors compared to Pumice. It has sharper edges.
text_Pumice: Resembles volcanic lava rock and is very light compared to Basalt. It has rougher grain and rounded edges.

text_Gabbro: Has a darker color overall and can have blocky sharp edges. It resembles granite and is darker than Peridotite.
text_Peridotite: It also resembles granite but is lighter in color. There is also some yellow/green present in some. It has grainy edges.
